decls.text: Forward declarations
Options for plots (see BeginPlot).

decls.name: ImPlotFlags_None
decls.docComment: default

decls.name: ImPlotFlags_NoTitle
decls.docComment: the plot title will not be displayed (titles are also hidden if preceeded by double hashes, e.g. "##MyPlot")

decls.name: ImPlotFlags_NoLegend
decls.docComment: the legend will not be displayed

decls.name: ImPlotFlags_NoMenus
decls.docComment: the user will not be able to open context menus with right-click

decls.name: ImPlotFlags_NoBoxSelect
decls.docComment: the user will not be able to box-select with right-click drag

decls.name: ImPlotFlags_NoMousePos
decls.docComment: the mouse position, in plot coordinates, will not be displayed inside of the plot

decls.name: ImPlotFlags_NoHighlight
decls.docComment: plot items will not be highlighted when their legend entry is hovered

decls.name: ImPlotFlags_NoChild
decls.docComment: a child window region will not be used to capture mouse scroll (can boost performance for single ImGui window applications)

decls.name: ImPlotFlags_Equal
decls.docComment: primary x and y axes will be constrained to have the same units/pixel (does not apply to auxiliary y-axes)

decls.name: ImPlotFlags_YAxis2
decls.docComment: enable a 2nd y-axis on the right side

decls.name: ImPlotFlags_YAxis3
decls.docComment: enable a 3rd y-axis on the right side

decls.name: ImPlotFlags_Query
decls.docComment: the user will be able to draw query rects with middle-mouse or CTRL + right-click drag

decls.name: ImPlotFlags_Crosshairs
decls.docComment: the default mouse cursor will be replaced with a crosshair when hovered

decls.name: ImPlotFlags_AntiAliased
decls.docComment: plot lines will be software anti-aliased (not recommended for high density plots, prefer MSAA)

decls.text: Options for plot axes (see BeginPlot).

decls.name: ImPlotAxisFlags_None
decls.docComment: default

decls.name: ImPlotAxisFlags_NoLabel
decls.docComment: the axis label will not be displayed (axis labels also hidden if the supplied string name is NULL)

decls.name: ImPlotAxisFlags_NoGridLines
decls.docComment: no grid lines will be displayed

decls.name: ImPlotAxisFlags_NoTickMarks
decls.docComment: no tick marks will be displayed

decls.name: ImPlotAxisFlags_NoTickLabels
decls.docComment: no text labels will be displayed

decls.name: ImPlotAxisFlags_Foreground
decls.docComment: grid lines will be displayed in the foreground (i.e. on top of data) in stead of the background

decls.name: ImPlotAxisFlags_LogScale
decls.docComment: a logartithmic (base 10) axis scale will be used (mutually exclusive with ImPlotAxisFlags_Time)

decls.name: ImPlotAxisFlags_Time
decls.docComment: axis will display date/time formatted labels (mutually exclusive with ImPlotAxisFlags_LogScale)

decls.name: ImPlotAxisFlags_Invert
decls.docComment: the axis will be inverted

decls.name: ImPlotAxisFlags_NoInitialFit
decls.docComment: axis will not be initially fit to data extents on the first rendered frame (also the case if SetNextPlotLimits explicitly called)

decls.name: ImPlotAxisFlags_AutoFit
decls.docComment: axis will be auto-fitting to data extents

decls.name: ImPlotAxisFlags_RangeFit
decls.docComment: axis will only fit points if the point is in the visible range of the **orthoganol** axis

decls.name: ImPlotAxisFlags_LockMin
decls.docComment: the axis minimum value will be locked when panning/zooming

decls.name: ImPlotAxisFlags_LockMax
decls.docComment: the axis maximum value will be locked when panning/zooming

decls.text: Options for subplots (see BeginSubplot).

decls.name: ImPlotSubplotFlags_None
decls.docComment: default

decls.name: ImPlotSubplotFlags_NoTitle
decls.docComment: the subplot title will not be displayed (titles are also hidden if preceeded by double hashes, e.g. "##MySubplot")

decls.name: ImPlotSubplotFlags_NoLegend
decls.docComment: the legend will not be displayed (only applicable if ImPlotSubplotFlags_ShareItems is enabled)

decls.name: ImPlotSubplotFlags_NoMenus
decls.docComment: the user will not be able to open context menus with right-click

decls.name: ImPlotSubplotFlags_NoResize
decls.docComment: resize splitters between subplot cells will be not be provided

decls.name: ImPlotSubplotFlags_NoAlign
decls.docComment: subplot edges will not be aligned vertically or horizontally

decls.name: ImPlotSubplotFlags_ShareItems
decls.docComment: items across all subplots will be shared and rendered into a single legend entry

decls.name: ImPlotSubplotFlags_LinkRows
decls.docComment: link the y-axis limits of all plots in each row (does not apply auxiliary y-axes)

decls.name: ImPlotSubplotFlags_LinkCols
decls.docComment: link the x-axis limits of all plots in each column

decls.name: ImPlotSubplotFlags_LinkAllX
decls.docComment: link the x-axis limits in every plot in the subplot

decls.name: ImPlotSubplotFlags_LinkAllY
decls.docComment: link the y-axis limits in every plot in the subplot (does not apply to auxiliary y-axes)

decls.name: ImPlotSubplotFlags_ColMajor
decls.docComment: subplots are added in column major order instead of the default row major order

decls.text: Plot styling colors.

decls.name: ImPlotCol_Line
decls.docComment: plot line/outline color (defaults to next unused color in current colormap)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_Fill
decls.docComment: plot fill color for bars (defaults to the current line color)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_MarkerOutline
decls.docComment: marker outline color (defaults to the current line color)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_MarkerFill
decls.docComment: marker fill color (defaults to the current line color)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_ErrorBar
decls.docComment: error bar color (defaults to ImGuiCol_Text)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_FrameBg
decls.docComment: plot frame background color (defaults to ImGuiCol_FrameBg)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_PlotBg
decls.docComment: plot area background color (defaults to ImGuiCol_WindowBg)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_PlotBorder
decls.docComment: plot area border color (defaults to ImGuiCol_Border)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_LegendBg
decls.docComment: legend background color (defaults to ImGuiCol_PopupBg)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_LegendBorder
decls.docComment: legend border color (defaults to ImPlotCol_PlotBorder)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_LegendText
decls.docComment: legend text color (defaults to ImPlotCol_InlayText)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_TitleText
decls.docComment: plot title text color (defaults to ImGuiCol_Text)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_InlayText
decls.docComment: color of text appearing inside of plots (defaults to ImGuiCol_Text)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_XAxis
decls.docComment: x-axis label and tick lables color (defaults to ImGuiCol_Text)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_XAxisGrid
decls.docComment: x-axis grid color (defaults to 25% ImPlotCol_XAxis)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_YAxis
decls.docComment: y-axis label and tick labels color (defaults to ImGuiCol_Text)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_YAxisGrid
decls.docComment: y-axis grid color (defaults to 25% ImPlotCol_YAxis)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_YAxis2
decls.docComment: 2nd y-axis label and tick labels color (defaults to ImGuiCol_Text)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_YAxisGrid2
decls.docComment: 2nd y-axis grid/label color (defaults to 25% ImPlotCol_YAxis2)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_YAxis3
decls.docComment: 3rd y-axis label and tick labels color (defaults to ImGuiCol_Text)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_YAxisGrid3
decls.docComment: 3rd y-axis grid/label color (defaults to 25% ImPlotCol_YAxis3)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_Selection
decls.docComment: box-selection color (defaults to yellow)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_Query
decls.docComment: box-query color (defaults to green)

decls.name: ImPlotCol_Crosshairs
decls.docComment: crosshairs color (defaults to ImPlotCol_PlotBorder)

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_Marker

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_MarkerSize

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_FillAlpha

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_ErrorBarSize
decls.docComment: float,  error bar whisker width in pixels

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_ErrorBarWeight
decls.docComment: float,  error bar whisker weight in pixels

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_DigitalBitHeight
decls.docComment: float,  digital channels bit height (at 1) in pixels

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_DigitalBitGap
decls.docComment: float,  digital channels bit padding gap in pixels

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_PlotBorderSize
decls.docComment: float,  thickness of border around plot area

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_MinorAlpha
decls.docComment: float,  alpha multiplier applied to minor axis grid lines

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_MajorTickLen
decls.docComment: ImVec2, major tick lengths for X and Y axes

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_MinorTickLen
decls.docComment: ImVec2, minor tick lengths for X and Y axes

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_MajorTickSize
decls.docComment: ImVec2, line thickness of major ticks

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_MinorTickSize
decls.docComment: ImVec2, line thickness of minor ticks

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_MajorGridSize
decls.docComment: ImVec2, line thickness of major grid lines

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_MinorGridSize
decls.docComment: ImVec2, line thickness of minor grid lines

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_PlotPadding
decls.docComment: ImVec2, padding between widget frame and plot area, labels, or outside legends (i.e. main padding)

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_LabelPadding
decls.docComment: ImVec2, padding between axes labels, tick labels, and plot edge

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_LegendPadding
decls.docComment: ImVec2, legend padding from plot edges

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_LegendInnerPadding
decls.docComment: ImVec2, legend inner padding from legend edges

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_LegendSpacing
decls.docComment: ImVec2, spacing between legend entries

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_MousePosPadding
decls.docComment: ImVec2, padding between plot edge and interior info text

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_AnnotationPadding
decls.docComment: ImVec2, text padding around annotation labels

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_FitPadding
decls.docComment: ImVec2, additional fit padding as a percentage of the fit extents (e.g. ImVec2(0.1f,0.1f) adds 10% to the fit extents of X and Y)

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_PlotDefaultSize
decls.docComment: ImVec2, default size used when ImVec2(0,0) is passed to BeginPlot

decls.name: ImPlotStyleVar_PlotMinSize
decls.docComment: ImVec2, minimum size plot frame can be when shrunk

ImPlot End-User API
Creates a new ImPlot context. Call this after ImGui::CreateContext.
Destroys an ImPlot context. Call this before ImGui::DestroyContext. NULL = destroy current context.
Returns the current ImPlot context. NULL if no context has ben set.
Sets the current ImPlot context.
Sets the current **ImGui** context. This is ONLY necessary if you are compiling
ImPlot as a DLL (not recommended) separate from your ImGui compilation. It
sets the global variable GImGui, which is not shared across DLL boundaries.
See GImGui documentation in imgui.cpp for more details.
Starts a 2D plotting context. If this function returns true, EndPlot() MUST
be called! You are encouraged to use the following convention:
if (BeginPlot(...)) {
ImPlot::PlotLine(...);
EndPlot();
Important notes:
- #title_id must be unique to the current ImGui ID scope. If you need to avoid ID
collisions or don't want to display a title in the plot, use double hashes
(e.g. "MyPlot##HiddenIdText" or "##NoTitle").
- If #x_label and/or #y_label are provided, axes labels will be displayed.
- #size is the **frame** size of the plot widget, not the plot area. The default
size of plots (i.e. when ImVec2(0,0)) can be modified in your ImPlotStyle
(default is 400x300 px).
- Auxiliary y-axes must be enabled with ImPlotFlags_YAxis2/3 to be displayed.
- See ImPlotFlags and ImPlotAxisFlags for more available options.
Only call EndPlot() if BeginPlot() returns true! Typically called at the end
of an if statement conditioned on BeginPlot(). See example above.
Starts a subdivided plotting context. If the function returns true,
EndSubplots() MUST be called! Call BeginPlot/EndPlot AT MOST [rows*cols]
times in  between the begining and end of the subplot context. Plots are
added in row major order.
Example:
if (BeginSubplots("My Subplot",2,3,ImVec2(800,400)) {
for (int i = 0; i
if (BeginPlot(...)) {
ImPlot::PlotLine(...);
EndPlot();
EndSubplots();
Produces:
Important notes:
- #title_id must be unique to the current ImGui ID scope. If you need to avoid ID
collisions or don't want to display a title in the plot, use double hashes
(e.g. "MyPlot##HiddenIdText" or "##NoTitle").
- #rows and #cols must be greater than 0.
- #size is the size of the entire grid of subplots, not the individual plots
- #row_ratios and #col_ratios must have AT LEAST #rows and #cols elements,
respectively. These are the sizes of the rows and columns expressed in ratios.
If the user adjusts the dimensions, the arrays are updated with new ratios.
Important notes regarding BeginPlot from inside of BeginSubplots:
- The #title_id parameter of _BeginPlot_ (see above) does NOT have to be
unique when called inside of a subplot context. Subplot IDs are hashed
for your convenience so you don't have call PushID or generate unique title
strings. Simply pass an empty string to BeginPlot unless you want to title
each subplot.
- The #size parameter of _BeginPlot_ (see above) is ignored when inside of a
subplot context. The actual size of the subplot will be based on the
#size value you pass to _BeginSubplots_ and #row/#col_ratios if provided.
Only call EndSubplots() if BeginSubplots() returns true! Typically called at the end
of an if statement conditioned on BeginSublots(). See example above.
Plots an axis-aligned image. #bounds_min/bounds_max are in plot coordinates (y-up) and #uv0/uv1 are in texture coordinates (y-down).
Plots a centered text label at point x,y with an optional pixel offset. Text color can be changed with ImPlot::PushStyleColor(ImPlotCol_InlayText, ...).
Plots a dummy item (i.e. adds a legend entry colored by ImPlotCol_Line)
Set the axes range limits of the next plot. Call right before BeginPlot(). If ImGuiCond_Always is used, the axes limits will be locked.
Set the X axis range limits of the next plot. Call right before BeginPlot(). If ImGuiCond_Always is used, the X axis limits will be locked.
Set the Y axis range limits of the next plot. Call right before BeginPlot(). If ImGuiCond_Always is used, the Y axis limits will be locked.
Links the next plot limits to external values. Set to NULL for no linkage. The pointer data must remain valid until the matching call to EndPlot.
Fits the next plot axes to all plotted data if they are unlocked (equivalent to double-clicks).
Set the X axis ticks and optionally the labels for the next plot. To keep the default ticks, set #keep_default=true.
Set the Y axis ticks and optionally the labels for the next plot. To keep the default ticks, set #keep_default=true.
Set the format for numeric X axis labels (default="%g"). Formated values will be doubles (i.e. don't supply %d, %i, etc.). Not applicable if ImPlotAxisFlags_Time enabled.
Set the format for numeric Y axis labels (default="%g"). Formated values will be doubles (i.e. don't supply %d, %i, etc.).
Select which Y axis will be used for subsequent plot elements. The default is ImPlotYAxis_1, or the first (left) Y axis. Enable 2nd and 3rd axes with ImPlotFlags_YAxisX.
Hides or shows the next plot item (i.e. as if it were toggled from the legend). Use ImGuiCond_Always if you need to forcefully set this every frame.
Convert pixels to a position in the current plot's coordinate system. A negative y_axis uses the current value of SetPlotYAxis (ImPlotYAxis_1 initially).
Convert a position in the current plot's coordinate system to pixels. A negative y_axis uses the current value of SetPlotYAxis (ImPlotYAxis_1 initially).
Get the current Plot position (top-left) in pixels.
Get the curent Plot size in pixels.
Returns true if the plot area in the current plot is hovered.

Returns true if the YAxis[n] plot area in the current plot is hovered.

Returns the current plot axis range. A negative y_axis uses the current value of SetPlotYAxis (ImPlotYAxis_1 initially).

Returns the current plot box selection bounds.

Add a new colormap. The color data will be copied. The colormap can be used by pushing either the returned index or the
string name with PushColormap. The colormap name must be unique and the size must be greater than 1. You will receive
an assert otherwise! By default colormaps are considered to be qualitative (i.e. discrete). If you want to create a
continuous colormap, set #qual=false. This will treat the colors you provide as keys, and ImPlot will build a linearly
interpolated lookup table. The memory footprint of this table will be exactly ((size-1)*255+1)*4 bytes.
Returns the number of available colormaps (i.e. the built-in + user-added count).
Returns a null terminated string name for a colormap given an index. Returns NULL if index is invalid.
Returns an index number for a colormap given a valid string name. Returns -1 if name is invalid.
Temporarily switch to one of the built-in (i.e. ImPlotColormap_XXX) or user-added colormaps (i.e. a return value of AddColormap). Don't forget to call PopColormap!
Push a colormap by string name. Use built-in names such as "Default", "Deep", "Jet", etc. or a string you provided to AddColormap. Don't forget to call PopColormap!
Undo temporary colormap modification(s). Undo multiple pushes at once by increasing count.
Returns the next color from the current colormap and advances the colormap for the current plot.
Can also be used with no return value to skip colors if desired. You need to call this between Begin/EndPlot!
Returns the size of a colormap.

Shows a button with a colormap gradient brackground.
When items in a plot sample their color from a colormap, the color is cached and does not change
unless explicitly overriden. Therefore, if you change the colormap after the item has already been plotted,
item colors will NOT update. If you need item colors to resample the new colormap, then use this
function to bust the cached colors. If #plot_title_id is NULL, then every item in EVERY existing plot
will be cache busted. Otherwise only the plot specified by #plot_title_id will be busted. For the
latter, this function must be called in the same ImGui ID scope that the plot is in. You should rarely if ever
need this function, but it is available for applications that require runtime colormap swaps (e.g. Heatmaps demo).
